-- SK Energy Says Explosion at Ulsan Heavy Oil Unit Kills One, Injures Six
-- B y   S h i n h y e   K a n g
-- 2010-12-20T04:39:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/sk-energy-says-explosion-at-ulsan-heavy-oil-unit-kills-one-injures-six.html
SK Energy Co., South Korea’s biggest
oil refiner, said an explosion hasn’t affected operations at its
heavy oil upgrade unit. One sub contractor died while six people
were hospitalized, Chung Tae Hoon, a spokesman at SK Energy said
by phone.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
